Yes, Saturday works better for me because the garden center is usually quieter before noon.

If you want, we can start with the herb section, then look at planters after that.

I checked the weather, and it looks mild enough for a long walk between stores.

Bring the measurements for your windowsill so we can compare sizes without guessing.

Also, let me know if you still want to stop for tea afterward because I can stay until early evening.

Sam's Club

 

Member update

Your Sam's points are set to expire tomorrow

Existing Members have $100 in Sam's points that expires this week. Please review and claim your $100 amount today so it can be used before the expiration window closes.

Review your points before the deadline

The Sam’s Cash Bonus Offers program is part of the Sam’s Club loyalty rewards program. Your current Sam's points balance includes $100 that needs attention now, as those points are expiring soon.

Once the expiration takes effect, that portion may no longer be available. Taking a moment to review the details today helps you confirm what is still included and ready for use.

See your $100 in Sam's points

This notice is intended for Sam's Club Members receiving an update regarding available loyalty rewards program points and their upcoming expiration timing.

I would take the earlier train if you want extra time before the museum gets busy.

From the station, the side entrance is easier and usually has a shorter line.

For lunch, the little cafe across the square has good soup and plenty of seating by the window.

If you are bringing your sketchbook, I can pack the folding stool like we discussed.

Send me your thoughts on timing later, and I will adjust the rest of the afternoon around it.

